President Biden is set to visit Wolfspeed, a semiconductor manufacturer in Durham, North Carolina, as part of his three-week Investing in America tour. The tour aims to highlight the administration's economic agenda, including job creation and strengthening supply chains. The President will announce that over $435 billion in private-sector manufacturing commitments have been made since he took office. He will also emphasize the potential negative impact of repealing the Inflation Reduction Act and cutting funding for manufacturing, research, and innovation. The article also mentions discussions on Mississippi and Tennessee, the impasse between the President and Speaker McCarthy on budget talks, the importance of addressing the debt limit, potential financial regulatory reforms, the issue of gun control, and the President's upcoming trip to Israel.